Currently, there are about 18,000 of these machines in the United States and Abbott plans to increase production to carry out 50,000 tests per day. In Taiwan, a test is being developed using a monoclonal antibody that is specifically bound to the protein of the nucleocapside (protein N) of the new coronavirus, with the hope that it can provide results within a period of 15 to 20 minutes as well as a rapid test for influenza.
In March 2020, the revision of the publications concluded that "Torax radiographs have little diagnostic value in the first stages, while the results of the TC [computerized Tomography] can be obtained even before symptoms occur".
