The proportion of people infected who do not have symptoms is unknown for the time being and is being studied. The Centres for Control and Prevention of Korean Diseases (KCDC) reported that 20 per cent of confirmed cases remained asymptomatic during hospitalization.
The National Health Commission of China began to include asymptomatic cases in daily cases on 1 April. Of the 166 infections of that day, 130 (78%) were asymptomatic when the test was performed.
